# ‚öôÔ∏è Backend Services - Microservices Ecosystem

This directory contains the source code for all the microservices that power the UNIFORUM platform.

## üß© Architecture Overview

The backend follows the **API Gateway Pattern**. All external requests are handled by **Nginx**, which acts as a reverse proxy, routing traffic to the appropriate internal microservice.

## üìã Service Catalog

| Service Name | Port (Internal) | Database Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Identity Service** | 8001 | PostgreSQL | Authentication, JWT Token generation, and Registration. |
| **Academic Service** | 8002 | PostgreSQL | Manages faculties, careers, and academic data. |
| **Forum Service** | 8003 | PostgreSQL | Handles discussion boards and forum topics. |
| **Post Service** | 8004 | **MongoDB** | Manages high-volume user posts (NoSQL). |
| **Reply Service** | 8005 | PostgreSQL | Handles nested replies and comments. |
| **Reaction Service** | 8006 | **Redis** | Real-time likes and reactions (In-Memory). |
| **Search Service** | 8007 | Redis (Cache) | Optimized search engine with caching. |
| **Notification Service**| 8008 | Queue/Logic | Asynchronous notification handling. |
| **Moderation Service** | 8009 | Logs | Auditing and content moderation logs. |
| **User Service** | 8010 | PostgreSQL | User profile management. |

## üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack

* **Language:** Python 3.9+
* **Framework:** FastAPI / Flask (depending on service)
* **Containerization:** Docker
* **Gateway:** Nginx